OL,6,FThis is up from 4.22 million the
OL,7,Fprevious year and is above the
OL,8,Fprevious high of 4.28 million in the
OL,9,Fyear to March 2020.
OL,11,FThe latest figure is the highest since
OL,12,Fcomparable records for the UK began in
OL,13,F2002/03.
OL,15,FA household is considered to be in
OL,16,Frelative poverty if it is below 60% of
OL,17,Fthe median income after housing costs.
