OL,6,FMeghan Meek-O'Connor, senior child
OL,7,Fpoverty policy adviser at Save the
OL,8,FChildren UK, said: "Today 4.3 million
OL,9,Fchildren are being failed. It is an
OL,10,Foutrage that 100,000 more children are
OL,11,Fin poverty ` they are being forgotten.
OL,13,F"These shocking figures should be an
OL,14,Furgent wake-up call to all of us,
OL,15,Fespecially the UK government.
OL,17,F"We cannot go on like this. There is
OL,18,Fno reason children should be going
OL,19,Fwithout food, heating, toys, or beds."
