OL,6,FBut Thursday's figures showed a rise
OL,7,Ffor the second year in a row, with
OL,8,F600,000 more people, half of them
OL,9,Fchildren, living in absolute poverty `
OL,10,Fequivalent to 25% of children.
OL,12,FThere were an estimated 11.99 million
OL,13,Fpeople in absolute poverty in the UK
OL,14,Fin the year to March 2023, up from
OL,15,F11.39 million the previous year.
OL,17,FJRF chief analyst Peter Matejic said:
OL,18,F"The annual poverty figures published
OL,19,Ftoday confirm that the government
OL,20,Ffailed to protect the most vulnerable
OL,21,Ffrom the cost-of-living crisis."
